summary: An email from an FBI Assistant Special Agent in Charge in New York discussing coordination between the Epstein case and another case, requesting a spreadsheet of remaining electronic materials to be searched and estimates for completion.

persons.name: A/Assistant Special Agent in Charge FBI New York
persons.role: FBI Assistant Special Agent in Charge
persons.context: Author of the email requesting coordination between the Epstein case and another case, and asking for a spreadsheet of remaining electronic materials and completion estimates.

keyFacts: The email indicates the Epstein case was a priority for the FBI as of April 2020.
Coordination was requested between the Epstein case team and another case team.
A spreadsheet of remaining electronic materials to be searched was needed.
Estimates for when the remaining work would be completed were requested.
The communication shows ongoing investigative activity related to the Epstein case well after his death.
